        "desc2": { "t": 0, "b": { "t": 2, "i": [{ "t": 3 }], "s": "The Rosetta Stone contains the same text in Hieroglyphic, Demotic, and Greek scripts, providing the key to understanding ancient Egyptian writing. Discovered by scholars in 1799, it allowed Jean-François Champollion to decode hieroglyphs, opening the study of Egyptian history and culture. It illustrates the Ptolemaic administrative system and religious decrees." } },
