        "desc2": { "t": 0, "b": { "t": 2, "i": [{ "t": 3 }], "s": "The Edwin Smith Papyrus provides detailed descriptions of trauma cases, diagnoses, and surgical treatments, including suturing and immobilization. It emphasizes observation and logical reasoning rather than magic, marking a highly advanced understanding of medicine. This document is the earliest known surgical text in the world and offers invaluable insights into ancient Egyptian medical practices." } },
